    <stitle>3200 Integrated Mobility Option Service Manual - Transfer Case</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Transfer Case</title>
        <para>The Transfer Case is a set of helical gears (driver, idler, driven) with a 1:1 overall ratio in a ribbed,
            sand cast aluminum gear case running in oil which serves to drop the driveline's centerline 250mm (9.85 in.)
            behind the transmission. This permits a lowered frame and therefore floor in the body being carried. The
            Transfer Case has support arms at the left and right sides (note the right side three bolt pad in Figure 5,
            left side is similar).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1001804" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Transfer Case, Front</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1001805" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Transfer Case, Right</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Lubricant:</emph>
            SAE 75W-90 Synthetic. Fill to overtop at upper plug, Figure 4, approximately 7 pints. Lower plug is Drain.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1001806" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Transfer Case Support, Left</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1001807" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Transfer Case Support, Lower</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1001808" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Transfer Case Support, Right</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The Transfer Case is mounted with two lateral support arms, one at the left side (Figure 6) and one at the
            right side (Figure 8). Note the right side three bolt pad in Figure 5, left is similar. The outer ends of
            these support arms are isolator mounted to support brackets welded to the dropped portions (drop brackets)
            of the side frame rails.
        </para>
        <para>A lower, longitudinal stabilizing / support arm (Figure 9) mounts at the left, rear side of the Transfer
            Case and runs aft to an isolator / bracket at cross member #3 (Figure 10, Figure 11).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1001809" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Stabilizing/Support Arm</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1001810" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001810.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. C'mbr #3/Brkt, Front</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1001811" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1001811.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. C'mbr #3/Brkt, Rear</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Reference sketches of Transfer Case mounting and Dropped Frame</emph>
        </para>
